Hotel Inspiration

Luxury Train Journeys

Travel to exciting destinations in style

There's something uniquely romantic about train travel—the rhythmic clatter of wheels on track, ever-changing landscapes framed by elegant windows, impeccable service in mahogany-panelled carriages. These legendary rail experiences transform the journey itself into the destination, reviving the golden age of travel.

Our Rail Collection

Iconic journeys aboard legendary trains

Italy

Orient Express La Dolce Vita

The newest jewel in the Orient Express crown takes passengers through Italy's most enchanting destinations—Rome, Venice, Tuscany, and Portofino. Gorgeous carriages inspired by 1960s Italian design evoke la dolce vita in every gilded detail.

New for 2025 Italian Routes 1960s Design
Begin Your Journey
Europe

Venice Simplon-Orient-Express

The world's most celebrated train journey connects London, Paris, and Venice in Art Deco splendour. Restored 1920s carriages, French haute cuisine, and white-gloved service recreate the glamour of a bygone era. An experience that transcends mere transportation.

Art Deco Paris-Venice Fine Dining
Begin Your Journey
South Africa

Rovos Rail

The most luxurious train in the world traverses Southern Africa's most spectacular landscapes. Victorian elegance, five-star cuisine, and routes connecting Cape Town to Pretoria, Victoria Falls, and beyond. Each suite features period detail and panoramic windows.

Victorian Style Safari Routes Private Suites
Begin Your Journey
Scotland

Belmond Royal Scotsman

A country house on wheels winds through the Scottish Highlands, stopping at whisky distilleries and ancient castles. Tweed-clad observation cars, traditional cuisine, and evenings of folk music capture the essence of Scotland in intimate luxury.

Scottish Highlands Whisky Tours Castle Visits
Begin Your Journey
Southeast Asia

Eastern & Oriental Express

Belmond's legendary Asian train connects Singapore, Malaysia, and Thailand through tropical landscapes, ancient temples, and colonial heritage. Teak-panelled cabins, Thai silk furnishings, and excursions to UNESCO sites make this the ultimate Southeast Asian journey.

Southeast Asia UNESCO Sites Observation Car
